# Claude Code Commands

This directory contains custom Claude Code commands for development workflow automation.

## Available Commands

### ci
Review GitHub Actions workflow runs, analyze failures, and provide actionable diagnostics.
Usage: /ci [workflow=<file|id>|all]

### commit  
Create well-formatted commits with conventional commit messages and emoji.
Reviews pre-commit issues before creating the commit.
Usage: /commit [topic]

### push
Review unpublished commits and check for sensitive information before pushing.
Ensures commits are ready for remote publication.
Usage: /push

## Usage
These commands are automatically available in Claude Code when this directory is in your .claude/commands path.